definition: abbr. for 柬埔寨[Jian3 pu3 zhai4], Cambodia
abbr. for 柬埔寨[Jian3 pu3 zhai4], Cambodia
variant of 書簡|书简[shu1 jian3]

sentences.english: Hu said that the Chinese and Cambodian peoples share a long history of friendly exchanges.
sentences.chinese: 胡锦涛说，中柬两国人民有着长期友好交往的历史。

sentences.english: He also expressed his heartfelt gratitude for China's unselfish assistance to Cambodia in the past years.
sentences.chinese: 他对中国多年来给予柬无私的援助表示衷心的感谢。

sentences.english: Even the Thai-Cambodian troops on both sides are at daggers drawn as people think.
sentences.chinese: 就连泰柬两边的驻军也没有人们想象的那样剑拔弩张。

sentences.english: The Chinese side will continue to help Cambodia train various professionals.
sentences.chinese: 中方将继续帮助柬培训各类专业人才。

sentences.english: Both the postcards and Ocean Engineering invitation cards do not have envelopes.
sentences.chinese: 静思语明信片及海洋工程系邀请柬都没有信封。

sentences.english: In the meeting with Hun Sen, Wen said, "China and Cambodia enjoy close ties.
sentences.chinese: 在会见洪森时，温家宝表示，中柬关系十分密切。

sentences.english: He expressed support for Cambodia's efforts to join the World Trade Organization and the Asia-Euro meeting.
sentences.chinese: 中国支持柬加入世贸组织和亚欧会议。

sentences.english: Wu said that China and Cambodia are close neighbors enjoying an over-2000-year history of friendly exchanges.
sentences.chinese: 吴邦国说，中柬是近邻，有两千多年的友好交往历史。

sentences.english: Physical compulsion or restraint was effectual, of course, while it lasted.
sentences.chinese: 当然，体罚和管柬在施行的当时还是有效的。

sentences.english: On the morning of the same day, Wen also laid a wreath at Cambodia's Monument to Independence.
sentences.chinese: 当天上午，温家宝还向柬独立纪念碑敬献了花圈。
